The '''Baruch Padeh Medical Center''' ({{lang-he|בית חולים ברוך פדה}}, ''Beit Holim Barukh Padeh''), formerly known as the '''Poriya Medical Center''', is a general [[hospital]] located in the region of [[Galilee]], in the state of [[Israel]], it was established in 1955 and it replaced the Schweitzer [[Hospital]] and the Maternity Hospital of the [[Church of Scotland|Scottish Church]] in [[Tiberias]].

